03:02.307 --> 03:03.809
‐ Is this an ambush?

03:03.809 --> 03:06.436
Because I already said I'm sorry.
It won't happen again.

03:06.436 --> 03:09.898
‐ It's not an ambush, mijo.
I'm here to talk to Adrian.

03:09.898 --> 03:12.401
Your mom and I thought I should be here
for the follow‐up conversation

03:12.401 --> 03:14.319
about you being gay.

03:15.404 --> 03:17.906
‐ Oh. Okay.

03:19.533 --> 03:20.909
‐ Papi's here?

03:20.909 --> 03:23.704
‐ Hey. [laughs] Yeah. Um...
ISABEL: Hey! [laughs]

03:23.704 --> 03:26.915
‐ Well, we all wanted to talk to you
about last night.

03:26.915 --> 03:32.546
‐ Yeah. Do you know
what it means to be... gay?

03:32.546 --> 03:37.134
‐ Yeah, of course.
Like Elliot Felter's two moms.

03:37.134 --> 03:39.469
‐ Yes! Exactly.

03:39.469 --> 03:41.972
‐ And Spongebob. Spongebob is gay.

03:41.972 --> 03:45.225
‐ No. He's a sponge.
‐ Oh, Mom.

03:46.476 --> 03:49.062
‐ Uh, well, do you have any questions?

03:49.062 --> 03:52.774
‐ Yeah. Why was Mia your girlfriend
if you're gay?

03:53.901 --> 03:56.612
‐ Uh... good question.

03:57.362 --> 04:00.282
I was still figuring some stuff out.

04:02.242 --> 04:05.245
‐ Sometimes people don't know
what they like until they try it.

04:05.245 --> 04:10.000
Um, like when you thought
blueberry pancakes were the best

04:10.000 --> 04:12.711
until you tried your mom's French toast.

04:14.254 --> 04:18.008
‐ Cool. Glad you found your French toast.

04:18.008 --> 04:20.511
‐ Thanks, papa. Me, too.

04:20.511 --> 04:25.098
